  <h1>
   path_get_x
  </h1>
  With this function you can get the x coordinate of a position on any given path. 0 is the start of the path, 1 is the end of the path, and anything in between equates to that far through the path. This needn't be a defining point of the path, it can be anywhere on it.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">path_get_x(ind, pos);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      index
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../The_Asset_Editors/Paths.htm">
        Path Asset
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The index of the path to check.
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      pos
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      How far through the path to check. Between 0 (start) and 1 (end).
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">x = path_get_x(pth_WallWalk, 0.5);
</code></pre>
  This will set the calling instance's x to the x coordinate of the point at exactly halfway through the given path.
 </body>
</html>